===Etymology 1===
Derived from the American-Spanish ''[[cimarrón]]'', meaning “[[fugitive]],” “[[wild]]”, “[[untamed]]”.

====Noun====
{{wikipedia|Maroon (people)}}
{{en-noun}}

# An escaped [[negro]] [[slave]] of the Caribbean and the Americas or a descendent of escaped slaves.
# A [[castaway]]; a person who has been marooned.

====Adjective====
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

# associated with Maroon culture, communities or peoples

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To abandon in a remote, desolate place, as on a deserted island.

